
ADR-007

Title

Use Dataclasses for Contracts

Context

The framework exchanges structured data between providers, validators, scorers and reporters.

Decision

Use immutable-style dataclasses to represent request and response contracts.

Consequences

Pros

✓ Better IDE support

✓ Type hints

✓ Easier testing

✓ Explicit contracts

Cons

• Slightly more boilerplate than dictionaries.